title: Google\Cloud\Dataproc\V1\GkeNodePoolConfig
name: GkeNodePoolConfig
description:
The configuration of a GKE NodePool used by a Dataproc-on-GKE cluster.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.dataproc.v1.GkeNodePoolConfig

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.locations
params.description: Optional. The list of Compute Engine zones where NodePool's nodes will be located. Note: Currently, only one zone may be specified. If a location is not specified during NodePool creation, Dataproc will choose a location.

params.name: data.autoscaling
params.description: Optional. The autoscaler configuration for this NodePool. The autoscaler is enabled only when a valid configuration is present.
